Organizing the poster
making sure content is distributed harmoniously
1) A good starting point could be to mentally split your poster into 9 equally sized fields. 
You could also do this physically with a thin almost invisible pencil.

Try Leaving 3 of them empty
2) Prioritize what is on the poster
3) Decide where to place elements
4) Size elements relatively to paper and each other
5) Verify that the poster is readable from the same distance as the audience will read it.
